{
  "message": "native: ALL 15 shaders pass conformance vs browser WebGPU\n\nFinal 3 ports:\n  - banded_attention (large kernel: GQA + sliding window + sinks)\n  - qmoe_gate_up (sparse MoE matmul, expert-strided int4 weights)\n  - qmoe_down_scatter (sparse MoE scatter-add via atomicCAS on\n    f32-bits-as-u32; tagged f32 for tolerance comparison since\n    atomic commit order differs across drivers)\n\n14 byte-equal vs browser; qmoe_down_scatter within 8e-7 relative\ndrift (atomic ordering, not a kernel bug). Every shader the\nWebGpuBackend uses is now ported to wgpu-native + Zig with\nend-to-end conformance against the browser-dumped fixture.\n\nNext: wire the shaders into a forward() entry point that loads\nweights from OPFS-cached ONNX, runs the full transformer, returns\nlogits \u2014 same shape the browser path produces.",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "87fcf846c254ab2311049940f8f444beaf143598",
      "filename": "tests/conformance/shaders.html",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 87,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 87,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/teamchong/textsift/blob/00c07e6d854663bc48f14d197dcfa460b7427ee8/tests%2Fconformance%2Fshaders.html",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/teamchong/textsift/raw/00c07e6d854663bc48f14d197dcfa460b7427ee8/tests%2Fconformance%2Fshaders.html",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/teamchong/textsift/contents/tests%2Fconformance%2Fshaders.html?ref=00c07e6d854663bc48f14d197dcfa460b7427ee8",
      "patch": "@@ -331,6 +331,93 @@\n             };\n           },\n         },\n+        {\n+          name: \"banded_attention\",\n+          build() {\n+            const T = 4, H_q = 4, H_kv = 2, head_dim = 32, window = 2, use_mask = 0;\n+            return {\n+              uniform: { binding: 0, bytes: dimsBuf([\n+                {tag:\"u32\",value:T},{tag:\"u32\",value:H_q},{tag:\"u32\",value:H_kv},{tag:\"u32\",value:head_dim},\n+                {tag:\"u32\",value:window},{tag:\"u32\",value:use_mask},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},\n+              ]) },\n+              inputs: [\n+                { binding: 1, name: \"q\", bytes: rngF16(70, T*H_q*head_dim, 0.3) },\n+                { binding: 2, name: \"k\", bytes: rngF16(71, T*H_kv*head_dim, 0.3) },\n+                { binding: 3, name: \"v\", bytes: rngF16(72, T*H_kv*head_dim, 0.3) },\n+                { binding: 4, name: \"sinks\", bytes: new Uint8Array(rngF32(73, H_q, 0.5).buffer) },\n+                // mask is unread when use_mask=0 but the binding must\n+                // still resolve to a non-empty storage buffer.\n+                { binding: 5, name: \"mask\", bytes: new Uint8Array(4) },\n+              ],\n+              output: { binding: 6, elements: T*H_q*head_dim, dtype: \"f16\" },\n+              dispatch: [T*H_q, 1, 1],\n+            };\n+          },\n+        },\n+        {\n+          name: \"qmoe_gate_up\",\n+          build() {\n+            const E = 4, T = 2, K = 2, N = 64, D = 64;\n+            const n_blocks = D / 32;\n+            const wNib = rngNibbles(80, E*N*D);\n+            return {\n+              uniform: { binding: 0, bytes: dimsBuf([\n+                {tag:\"u32\",value:T},{tag:\"u32\",value:K},{tag:\"u32\",value:N},{tag:\"u32\",value:D},\n+                {tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},\n+              ]) },\n+              inputs: [\n+                { binding: 1, name: \"x\", bytes: new Uint8Array(rngF32(81, T*D, 0.3).buffer) },\n+                // routing_idx: every (token, k_pick) routes to expert (k_pick % E).\n+                { binding: 2, name: \"routing_idx\", bytes: (() => {\n+                  const a = new Int32Array(T*K);\n+                  for (let i = 0; i < T*K; i++) a[i] = i % E;\n+                  return new Uint8Array(a.buffer);\n+                })() },\n+                { binding: 3, name: \"w_int4\", bytes: packNibbles(wNib) },\n+                { binding: 4, name: \"w_scales\", bytes: rngF16(82, E*N*n_blocks, 1.0) },\n+                { binding: 5, name: \"w_zp\", bytes: packZp(E*N, n_blocks, 83) },\n+                { binding: 6, name: \"bias\", bytes: rngF16(84, E*N, 0.1) },\n+              ],\n+              output: { binding: 7, elements: T*K*N, dtype: \"f32\" },\n+              dispatch: [T*K, Math.ceil(N / 64), 1],\n+            };\n+          },\n+        },\n+        {\n+          name: \"qmoe_down_scatter\",\n+          build() {\n+            const E = 4, T = 2, K = 2, N = 64, D = 64;\n+            const n_blocks = N / 32;\n+            const wNib = rngNibbles(90, E*D*N);\n+            return {\n+              uniform: { binding: 0, bytes: dimsBuf([\n+                {tag:\"u32\",value:T},{tag:\"u32\",value:K},{tag:\"u32\",value:N},{tag:\"u32\",value:D},\n+                {tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},{tag:\"u32\",value:0},\n+              ]) },\n+              inputs: [\n+                { binding: 1, name: \"glu\", bytes: new Uint8Array(rngF32(91, T*K*N, 0.3).buffer) },\n+                { binding: 2, name: \"routing_idx\", bytes: (() => {\n+                  const a = new Int32Array(T*K);\n+                  for (let i = 0; i < T*K; i++) a[i] = i % E;\n+                  return new Uint8Array(a.buffer);\n+                })() },\n+                { binding: 3, name: \"routing_scores\", bytes: new Uint8Array(rngF32(92, T*K, 0.5).buffer) },\n+                { binding: 4, name: \"w_int4\", bytes: packNibbles(wNib) },\n+                { binding: 5, name: \"w_scales\", bytes: rngF16(93, E*D*n_blocks, 1.0) },\n+                { binding: 6, name: \"w_zp\", bytes: packZp(E*D, n_blocks, 94) },\n+                { binding: 7, name: \"bias\", bytes: rngF16(95, E*D, 0.1) },\n+              ],\n+              // acc is declared atomic<u32> in WGSL (the shader uses\n+              // atomicCAS on f32-bits-as-u32 to scatter-add). The bytes\n+              // ARE float values; tag as f32 so the harness compares\n+              // with fp tolerance \u2014 atomic commit order differs across\n+              // drivers and a single-ULP drift is expected.\n+              output: { binding: 8, elements: T*D, dtype: \"f32\" },\n+              outputInitial: new Uint8Array(T*D*4),\n+              dispatch: [T*K, Math.ceil(D / 64), 1],\n+            };\n+          },\n+        },\n       ];\n \n       try {"
    },
